# HIMS Frontend — PRODUCTION / CLOUD environment
#
# This file is a reference only — it is NOT read automatically during a
# Cloudflare Pages build. Cloudflare Pages injects environment variables via
# its own dashboard/CLI mechanism (see CLOUDFLARE_DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md, Step 4),
# not via a committed .env file. This file exists so the required variable
# name/shape is documented alongside .env.local.example.
#
# https:// is REQUIRED — himsApi.js throws a hard runtime error on http://
# or a missing value. This is a locked decision (see LOCAL_FRONTEND_GUIDE.md).
#
# Set this exact variable in the Cloudflare Pages dashboard:
#   Workers & Pages → your project → Settings → Environment variables
#     Name:  VITE_API_URL
#     Value: https://api.yourhospital.com   (your real backend origin, https only)
#
# Do NOT commit a real .env.production file with a live backend URL to git —
# keep the actual value only in the Cloudflare Pages dashboard/CLI secret store.
VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourhospital.com
